==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*leubo-'', from Indo-European ''*leubh-'' ‘love’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[liof]] (Dutch [[lief#Dutch|lief]]), Old High German [[liub]] (German [[lieb]]), Old Norse [[ljúfr]] (Swedish [[ljuv]]), Gothic [[𐌻𐌹𐌿𐍆𐍃]].  Related to [[lufu]], [[lufian]], [[lof]].

